  "prompt": "What is colour of water?",
  "response": "Pure water is colorless when observed in small quantities. However, in larger volumes, such as a lake or ocean, it can appear to have a blue tint. This is because water absorbs colors at the red end of the light spectrum and reflects and scatters the blue, giving large bodies of water their characteristic blue appearance. Factors such as impurities, algae, and sunlight can also affect the color of water you observe.",
